12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
13
14 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Driving privilege card -- eligibility. (1) (a) As used in [sections 1
15 through 5] and except as provided in subsections (1)(b) and (1)(c), "driving privilege card" means an
16 identification card that conveys permission to operate a motor vehicle.
17 (b) A motorcycle endorsement is necessary to operate a motorcycle.
18 (c) A driving privilege card may not be used to operate a commercial motor vehicle.
19 (2) A person who is ineligible for a driver's license under 61-5-105(10) is eligible for a driving
20 privilege card.
21
22
23
24 (3) (a) Except as provided in subsection (3)(b), a driving privilege card expires 2 years after
25 issuance.
26 (b) A driving privilege card issued to a person who is 19 or 20 years of age expires on the person's
27 21st birthday.
28 (4) A driving privilege card may not be issued to a person:
